OL,4,Ccompensation for infected blood victims
OL,6,FNHS England chief executive Amanda
OL,7,FPritchard has also apologised to
OL,8,Fvictims of the scandal on behalf of
OL,9,Fthe health service in England, adding
OL,10,Fthat people "put their trust in the
OL,11,Fcare they got from the NHS over many
OL,12,Fyears, and they were badly let down".
OL,14,FAfter a decades-long battle for
OL,15,Fjustice, campaigners welcomed the
OL,16,Fprobe's recommendations but lamented
OL,17,Fthe fact delays meant many of those
OL,18,Fresponsible would never be held to
OL,19,Faccount.
