OL,6,FClive Smith, chairman of The
OL,7,FHaemophilia Society and also a
OL,8,Fcriminal barrister, said: "One of the
OL,9,Faspects that, sadly, the delay has
OL,10,Fcaused is the fact that there are
OL,11,Fdoctors out there who should have been
OL,12,Fprosecuted for manslaughter, gross
OL,13,Fnegligence manslaughter, doctors who
OL,14,Fwere testing their patients for HIV
OL,15,Fwithout consent, not telling them
OL,16,Fabout their infections.
OL,18,F"Those people should have been in the
OL,19,Fdock for gross negligence manslaughter.
