OL,6,FThe 2,527-page report from the
OL,7,Finquiry, published on Monday, found
OL,8,Fthat the infected blood scandal "could
OL,9,Flargely have been avoided" and there
OL,10,Fwas a "pervasive" cover-up to hide the
OL,11,Ftruth.
OL,13,FDeliberate attempts were made to
OL,14,Fconceal the disaster, including
OL,15,Fevidence of Whitehall officials
OL,16,Fdestroying documents, the seven-year
OL,17,Fprobe found.
OL,19,FPatients were knowingly exposed to
OL,20,Funacceptable risks of infection.
