OL,6,FInquiry chairman Sir Brian Langstaff
OL,7,Fsaid "the scale of what happened is
OL,8,Fhorrifying", with more than 3,000
OL,9,Fpeople dead as a result and survivors
OL,10,Fbattling for decades to uncover the
OL,11,Ftruth.
OL,13,FHe said the "level of suffering is
OL,14,Fdifficult to comprehend" and that the
OL,15,Fharms done to people have been
OL,16,Fcompounded by the reaction of
OL,17,Fsuccessive governments, the NHS and
OL,18,Fthe medical profession.
